JOBURG cops are looking for four men that were involved in a botched hijacking in Blairgowrie. A man was reversing out of his driveway when three of the four men got out of a white vehicle and approached the man's VW Polo. But the quick-thinking man reversed towards them, knocking the tail end of their vehicle instead. The men got back into the white vehicle and fled. According to Linden police station spokesperson, Constable Takalani Matumba an attempted robbery with firearms case has been opened. Matumba told News24 that said the police were actively looking for the suspects. 